batchBurnTokens(address,address[],uint25.details: Burns tokens from different addresses in a batch operation.

params._amounts: The list of amounts to be burned.
params._fromList: The list of addresses whose tokens will be burned.
params._token: The address of the token being burned.
params.orderIDs: The list of order IDs associated with the burning. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent of the token can call this function. Emits multiple {TokensBurned} events.

batchForceTransferTokens(address,address.details: Forcefully transfers tokens from one address to another for multiple users.

params._amounts: The list of token amounts to be transferred.
params.orderIDs: The list of order IDs associated with the forced transfer. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent or transfer agent (TA) can call this function. Emits multiple {ForceTransferred} events.

batchFreezePartialTokens(address,address.details: Freezes a partial amount of tokens for multiple users.

params._amounts: The list of token amounts to be frozen.
params.orderIDs: The list of order IDs associated with the freezing. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent or transfer agent (TA) can call this function. Emits multiple {UserTokensFrozen} events.

batchMintTokens(address,address[],uint25.details: Mints tokens to different addresses in a batch operation.

params._amounts: The list of amounts to be minted.
params._token: The address of the token being minted.
params.orderIDs: The list of order IDs associated with the minting. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent of the token can call this function. Emits multiple {TokensMinted} events.

batchRedemptionAndBurn(address,address[].details: Processes multiple redemptions and token burns in a batch.

params._burnAmount: An array of burn amounts corresponding to users.
params._principalAmount: An array of principal amounts corresponding to users.
params._profitAmount: An array of profit amounts corresponding to users.
params._token: The address of the token being burned.
params.orderID: An array of order IDs for the redemptions. Requirements: - All input arrays must have the same length. Calls `redemptionAndBurn` for each order in the batch.

batchRegisterIdentity(address[],address[.details: Registers multiple user identities in batch.

params._onchainID: The list of corresponding on-chain identities.
params._token: The address of the token. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - The caller must be an Identity Registry Agent. Emits multiple {UserIdentityRegistered} events.

batchSetAddressFrozen(address,address[],.details: Freezes or unfreezes multiple user addresses.

params._freeze: The list of boolean values indicating whether to freeze (true) or unfreeze (false) each user.
params.actionIDs: The list of action IDs associated with the freezing/unfreezing. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent of the token can call this function. Emits multiple {UserAddressFrozen} events.

batchSettlement(string[]).details: Settles multiple orders in a batch.

params.orderIDs: An array of order IDs to be settled. Calls `settlement` function for each order in the batch.

batchShareDividend(address,address[],uin.details: Distributes dividends to multiple users in batch.

params._dividendIds: The list of dividend distribution IDs.
params._fund: The address of the fund distributing the dividends.
params.stableCoin_: The stablecoin used for dividend distribution. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only an authorized agent can call this function. Emits multiple {DividendDistributed} events.

batchUnFreezePartialTokens(address,addre.details: Unfreezes a partial amount of tokens for multiple users.

params._amounts: The list of token amounts to be unfrozen.
params.orderIDs: The list of order IDs associated with the unfreezing. Requirements: - All input arrays must be of the same length. - Only the agent or transfer agent (TA) can call this function. Emits multiple {UserTokensUnFrozen} events.

callDeleteIdentity(address,address,strin.details: Deletes a user's identity from the identity registry.

params._token: The address of the token contract linked to the identity registry.
params._userAddress: The address of the user whose identity is being removed.
params.actionID: The identifier for the deletion action. Requirements: - Caller must be an Identity Registry Agent. Emits a {UserIdentityDeleted} event.

callUpdateCountry(address,uint16,address.details: Updates the country code of a user in the identity registry.

params._country: The new country code to be assigned.
params._token: The address of the token contract linked to the identity registry.
params._userAddress: The address of the user whose country code is being updated.
params.actionID: The identifier for the update action. Requirements: - Caller must be an Identity Registry Agent. Emits a {UserCountryUpdated} event.

callUpdateIdentity(address,address,addre.details: Updates the identity of a user in the identity registry.

params._identity: The new identity contract associated with the user.
params._token: The address of the token contract linked to the identity registry.
params._userAddress: The address of the user whose identity is being updated.
params.actionID: The identifier for the update action. Requirements: - Caller must be an Identity Registry Agent. Emits an {IdentityUpdated} event.

cancelOrder(string).details: Cancels an order, removing its pending amount and marking it as settled.

params.orderID: The unique identifier of the order to be canceled. Requirements: - Only the order creator (investor) can cancel it. - The order must not have been executed already. Emits an {OrderCancelled} event.

deposit(address,uint256,uint256,string,s.details: Deposits stablecoins into the escrow contract for an asset purchase.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

redemptionAndBurn(address,address,uint25.details: Handles token redemption by burning the investor’s tokens and transferring stablecoin back.

params._burnAmount: The amount of tokens to be burned.
params._principalAmount: The principal amount to be returned.
params._token: The address of the token to be burned.
params.coin: The stablecoin used for the transaction.
params.orderID: The unique identifier of the redemption order. Requirements: - The asset must be deployed by the sender. - Token address must not be zero. - Burn and principal amounts must be greater than zero. - Stablecoin must be supported. - Order ID must not have been processed already. Emits a {RedemptionAndBurn} event.

rejectOrder(string).details: Rejects an order by marking it as settled and removing its pending amount.

params.orderID: The unique identifier of the order to be rejected. Requirements: - Only the agent of the asset can reject the order. - The order must exist. - The order must not already be executed. Emits an {OrderRejected} event.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

rescueAnyERC20Tokens(address,address,uin.details: Allows the owner to rescue any ERC20 tokens sent to the contract.

setFundFactory(address).details: Sets the fund factory contract address.

params._fundFactory: The new fund factory contract address. Requirements: - Only the owner can call this function. - The address cannot be zero. Emits a {FundFactoryUpdated} event.

setMasterFactory(address).details: Sets the master factory contract address.

params._masterFactory: The new master factory contract address. Requirements: - Only the owner can call this function. - The address cannot be zero. Emits a {MasterFactoryUpdated} event.

setNAV(address,uint256,string).details: Updates the Net Asset Value (NAV) of a given token.

params.actionID: The identifier for the NAV update action. Requirements: - Only the agent of the token can call this function. - The token address cannot be zero. Emits a {NAVUpdated} event.

setStableCoin(string,address).details: Sets a stablecoin address for a specific currency.

params._stablecoin: The contract address of the stablecoin. Requirements: - Only the owner can call this function. - The stablecoin address cannot be zero. - The stablecoin for the given symbol should not already be set. Emits a {StableCoinUpdated} event.

setValuation(address,uint256,string).details: Updates the valuation of a given token.

params.actionID: The identifier for the valuation update action. Requirements: - Only the agent of the token can call this function. - The token address cannot be zero. Emits a {ValuationUpdated} event.

settlement(string).details: Settles an order by transferring funds from the investor to the agent and admin,       and mints tokens to the investor.

params.orderID: The unique identifier of the order to be settled. Requirements: - The order must exist. - The order must not already be settled. - Transfers the net amount to the agent. - Transfers the escrow fee to the admin. - Mints the corresponding tokens to the investor. Emits an {OrderSettled} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
